10 Section 2. Section 20-7-1506, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "20-7-1506. Incentives for creation of advanced opportunity programs. (1) A district that satisfies
12 the conditions of subsection (2) and is qualified by the board of public education pursuant to subsection (3) is
13 eligible for the funding and flexibilities in subsections (4) and (5).
14 (2) (a) To qualify for the funding and flexibilities in subsections (4) and (5), the board of trustees of
15 a district shall submit an application that has been approved by motion of the board and signed by the presiding
16 officer to the board of public education for approval of an advanced opportunity program on a form provided by
17 the superintendent of public instruction.
18 (b) The school board's application must include a strategic plan with appropriate planning horizons
19 for implementation, measurable objectives to ensure accountability, and planned strategies to:
20 (i) develop an advanced opportunity plan for each participating pupil from grades 6 through 12
21 that fosters individualized pathways for career and postsecondary educational opportunities and that honors
22 individual interests, passions, strengths, needs, and culture and is supported through relationships among
23 teachers, family, peers, the business community, postsecondary education officials, and other community
24 stakeholders;
25 (ii) embed community-based, experiential, online, and work-based learning opportunities and
26 foster a learning environment that incorporates both face-to-face and virtual connections; and
27 (iii) ensure equality of educational opportunity to participate by all qualifying pupils of the district.
